e Curious Case of a Supposed Karl Rove Quote Used on The National's New Album 'Sleep Well Beast<span style=\"padding-right:0.2em;\">'</span>\"</a>. <i>Newsweek</i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Newsweek&amp;rft.atitle=The+Curious+Case+of+a+Supposed+Karl+Rove+Quote+Used+on+The+National%27s+New+Album+%27Sleep+Well+Beast%27&amp;rft.date=2017-09-08&amp;rft.aulast=Schonfeld&amp;rft.aufirst=Zach&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsweek.com%2Fnational-sleep-well-beast-karl-rove-662307&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReality-based+community\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Zelizer, Julian E. (2010). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=MeO8b6S9lb4C&amp;pg=PA199&amp;dq=Reality-based+community&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjg_4mbt73XAhVDSSYKHYywCqkQ6AEILTAB#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\"><i>The Presidency of George W. Bush: A First Historical Assessment</i></a>. New Jersey: Princeton University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780691149011\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780691149011\">9780691149011</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Limbaugh, David (2007). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=eDUXAJ01h9AC&amp;lpg=PA337&amp;dq=Reality-based%20community&amp;pg=PA337#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\"><i>Bankrupt: The Intellectual and Moral Bankruptcy of Today's Democratic Party</i></a>. Washington, D.C.: Regnery Publishing, p. 337. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781596980174\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781596980174\">9781596980174</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Bruce Bartlett (November 26, 2012). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.theamericanconservative.com/articles/revenge-of-the-reality-based-community/\">Revenge of the Reality-Based Community: My life on the Republican right\u2014and how I saw it all go wrong</a>, <i>The American Conservative</i>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Damon Linker (January 27, 2016). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://theweek.com/articles/601420/left-vs-realitybased-community\">The left vs. the reality-based community</a>, <i>TheWeek.com.</i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-10\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Andersen, Kurt (September 2017). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2017/09/how-america-lost-its-mind/534231/\">How America Lost Its Mind: The nation\u2019s current post-truth moment is the ultimate expression of mind-sets that have made America exceptional throughout its history</a>, <i>The Atlantic</i>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-11\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Pennycook, Alastair (2017). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=1WA1DwAAQBAJ&amp;lpg=PT181&amp;dq=Reality-based%20community&amp;pg=PT181#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\"><i>Posthumanist Applied Linguistics</i></a>. New York, NY: Routledge. <a href=\"/wiki/Internat